      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 153: This still may not unblock the deadlock on Linux because NAT-PMP uses an unconnected UDP socket; shutdown(SHUT_RDWR) on an unconnected datagram socket can fail with ENOTCONN and not wake poll(). Since the actual closenatpmp() is dispatched onto the same io_context that may currently be blocked in readResponse(), the terminate callback may never run until poll() times out. Use a reliable wake mechanism instead, e.g. poll an additional self-pipe/eventfd/cancel fd that terminate() writes to from the caller thread, or make readResponse() use bounded short poll intervals while checking shutdownRequested_.\n```suggestion\n// Example direction: poll both the NAT-PMP socket and a shutdown wake fd,\n// and write to that fd from terminate() before dispatching cleanup.\n```",
